com.igeekinc.firehose

Class FirehoseChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.igeekinc.firehose.FirehoseChannel
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SSLFirehoseChannel

    public class FirehoseChannel
extends java.lang.Object
    FirehoseChannel provides a subset of java.nio.Channel operations suitable for Firehose operations. FirehoseChannel exists so that SSLFirehoseChannel can be implemented. Currently, reads are non-blocking while writes will block
    Author:
    David L. Smith-Uchida

      • readNoBlock

        public int readNoBlock(int forceReadAmount)
                throws java.io.IOException
        Will either read more data from the socket or just return if data is available in the input buffer
        Parameters:
        forceReadAmount - If forceReadAmount is more than the number of bytes in the inputBuffer, a read will be forced. May return more or less than the number of bytes requested
        Returns:
        Throws:
